== Replication Methodology for Heterogeneous Disease
<sec:replication-heterogeneous>

ME/CFS, like other multisystem chronic illnesses, exhibits profound treatment heterogeneity. Conventional randomized controlled trials powered to detect average treatment effects frequently fail despite strong mechanistic rationale and robust phase II data. This section examines why average-effect replication fails in heterogeneous diseases and proposes advanced designs—basket trials, umbrella trials, adaptive enrichment, and N-of-1 aggregation—suited to ME/CFS subgroup structure.

